curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/5946' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM9154", "table_name": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION", "content": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION  The SGM9154 is a 1-channel, 6th-order output  reconstruction filter which can operate from 3.1V to  5.5V single power supply. It is designed to replace  passive LC filters and drivers with an integrated device.  One channel is High Definition (HDp) filter.  The device allows DC- or AC-coupled output.  SGM9154 can be DC-coupled or AC-coupled with input  video signal to eliminate out-of-band noise, such as the  output stage of DAC. Internal bias circuitry may be  used for providing constant bias voltage if AC-coupled  inputs are required.  The SGM9154 is available in Green TSSOP-8 and  SOT-23-6 and SC70-5 packages. It operates over an  ambient temperature range of -40℃ to +85℃.    "}'
